meta_classes.name: Temporal Structure
meta_classes.description: Entities with modular composition that unfold or evolve over time. Common in processes, narratives, sequences, and dynamic systems.

meta_classes.name: Active Synthetic Object
meta_classes.description: Manufactured physical entities that exhibit autonomous behavior while being composed of observable matter. Includes machines, vehicles, robots, and powered devices.

meta_classes.name: Dynamic Effector
meta_classes.description: Entities that produce measurable effects and undergo internal state changes. Includes tools, processors, and transformative systems.

meta_classes.name: Institutional Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities defined by formal rules and subject to regulatory frameworks. Includes official categories, licensed items, and institutionally recognized objects.

meta_classes.name: Modular Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities with structured parts or hierarchical organization. Common in systems, collections, and composite structures.

meta_classes.name: Non-Physical Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities without physical attributes. Includes abstract concepts, ideas, processes, and purely informational objects.

meta_classes.name: Concrete Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities without abstract/symbolic qualities. Represents tangible, literal objects without representational or meta-level properties.

meta_classes.name: Human Interface
meta_classes.description: Entities deliberately designed for human interaction and use. Includes consumer products, user interfaces, and personal tools.

meta_classes.name: Static Artifact
meta_classes.description: Manufactured observable objects that are passive (not self-acting). Includes furniture, structures, containers, and static equipment.

meta_classes.name: Passive Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities without functional attributes. Neither designed for a purpose nor producing effects. Includes natural objects and raw materials.

meta_classes.name: Economic Institution
meta_classes.description: Socially constructed entities that are institutionally defined, regulated, and economically significant. Includes currencies, financial instruments, and commercial entities.

meta_classes.name: Natural Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities without social attributes. Exists independently of human social constructs, institutions, or economic systems.

meta_classes.name: Economic Asset
meta_classes.description: Entities with economic value or market impact. Includes commodities, resources, and tradeable items.

meta_classes.name: Regulated Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities subject to rules, norms, or formal regulation. Includes controlled substances, licensed activities, and standardized objects.

meta_classes.name: Observable Phenomenon
meta_classes.description: Entities detectable by senses or instruments but lacking other physical traits. Includes phenomena, events, and observable patterns.

meta_classes.name: Regulated Asset
meta_classes.description: Economically significant entities under regulatory control. Includes securities, controlled goods, and regulated commodities.

meta_classes.name: Temporal Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities defined primarily by their relationship to time. Includes events, periods, schedules, and time-bound phenomena.

meta_classes.name: Interactive Tool
meta_classes.description: Purpose-built entities that produce effects through human interaction. Includes hand tools, appliances, and user-operated equipment.

meta_classes.name: Social Construct
meta_classes.description: Entities that exist by collective agreement or shared understanding. Includes roles, statuses, conventions, and cultural concepts.

meta_classes.name: Active Biological Entity
meta_classes.description: Living or bio-inspired physical entities that exhibit autonomous behavior. Includes organisms, bio-robots, and organic active systems.

meta_classes.name: Designed Artifact
meta_classes.description: Entities created with deliberate purpose but without specific output effects. Includes decorative objects, art, and purposeful but passive items.

meta_classes.name: Institutional Category
meta_classes.description: Entities defined by formal institutions but not necessarily regulated. Includes official classifications, standards, and institutional types.

meta_classes.name: Powered Artifact
meta_classes.description: Manufactured objects that require external power but are not self-acting. Includes electrical appliances, powered displays, and energy-dependent equipment.

meta_classes.name: System Component
meta_classes.description: Purpose-built entities designed to function within larger systems. Includes parts, modules, and integrated components.

meta_classes.name: Hybrid Material
meta_classes.description: Entities combining synthetic and biological properties. Includes bio-plastics, organic electronics, and bio-synthetic composites.

meta_classes.name: Natural Active Object
meta_classes.description: Non-synthetic physical entities that exhibit autonomous behavior. Includes natural phenomena, living organisms, and self-moving natural objects.

meta_classes.name: Processing System
meta_classes.description: Purpose-built entities that transform inputs into outputs with state changes. Includes processors, converters, and transformation machinery.

meta_classes.name: Formal Institution
meta_classes.description: Socially constructed entities with formal institutional definition. Includes organizations, official bodies, and recognized institutions.

meta_classes.name: Economic Category
meta_classes.description: Institutionally defined entities with economic significance. Includes product categories, market segments, and trade classifications.

meta_classes.name: Integrated Interface
meta_classes.description: Purpose-built entities for human interaction within larger systems. Includes control panels, dashboards, and integrated user interfaces.

meta_classes.name: Structured Signal
meta_classes.description: Entities that convey information through modular structure. Includes coded messages, formatted data, and structured communications.

meta_classes.name: Signal Entity
meta_classes.description: Entities primarily serving to convey information or meaning. Includes signs, symbols, indicators, and communicative objects.

meta_classes.name: Formal System
meta_classes.description: Entities with rule-based modular structure. Includes protocols, grammars, logical systems, and formal languages.

meta_classes.name: Formal Language
meta_classes.description: Structured signalling systems governed by explicit rules. Includes programming languages, formal notations, and codified communication systems.

cross_domain.name: Regulated Industrial Machine
cross_domain.description: Active manufactured devices that produce outputs and undergo state changes, with temporal dynamics and institutional regulation. The dominant archetype for industrial equipment, power tools, and regulated machinery.

cross_domain.name: Regulated Active Device
cross_domain.description: Active synthetic devices under regulatory oversight that produce effects over time. Similar to industrial machines but without institutional definition requirements.

cross_domain.name: Interactive Industrial System
cross_domain.description: Human-interactive active devices designed for specific purposes, producing effects and changing state under institutional regulation. Includes control panels, operating machinery, and interactive industrial equipment.

cross_domain.name: Signalling Industrial Device
cross_domain.description: Active synthetic devices that transmit signals while producing effects, under institutional regulation. Includes communication equipment, sensors, and broadcasting machinery.

cross_domain.name: Bio-Industrial Artifact
cross_domain.description: Passive biomimetic or biological manufactured objects that produce effects under institutional regulation. Includes bio-engineered products, medical devices, and organic industrial materials.

emergent.name: Self-Referential Abstraction
emergent.description: Extremely rare entities with the Meta trait - concepts that refer to or describe themselves or other concepts. Only 0.3% of entities have this trait.
emergent.insight: Meta almost never co-occurs with Physical traits - self-referential concepts are purely abstract

emergent.name: Load-Bearing Structure
emergent.description: Rare physical entities with internal structural properties. Only 1.5% of entities have this trait - includes buildings, bridges, and engineered frameworks.
emergent.insight: Structural entities rarely have Social or Abstract traits - pure engineering focus

emergent.name: Critical Infrastructure
emergent.description: Entities essential for larger system function. Only 3% of entities - includes core components, foundational services, and irreplaceable system elements.
emergent.insight: System-Essential correlates strongly with Regulated - critical things need rules

emergent.name: Pure Abstraction
emergent.description: Entities with no physical traits whatsoever (Physical layer = 00). Includes concepts, ideas, processes, and mathematical objects.
emergent.insight: 16% of entities have zero physical traits - a substantial 'idea space'

emergent.name: Regulated Effector
emergent.description: Entities that produce effects AND are subject to regulation. This is the strongest Functional→Social correlation - 45% of effect-producing entities are regulated.
emergent.insight: Strong emergent pattern: things that DO things get RULES - regulatory capture is ontological

emergent.name: Observable Composite
emergent.description: Things you can see that have internal structure. Strongest Physical→Abstract correlation - 77% of observable things have compositional structure.
emergent.insight: Visibility and structure are deeply linked - we perceive things AS structured

emergent.name: Ritual Object
emergent.description: Entities with ritualistic or ceremonial significance. Only 5% of entities - includes religious items, ceremonial objects, and cultural artifacts.
emergent.insight: Ritualised correlates with Identity-Linked and Social Construct - rituals define group identity

emergent.name: Digital Entity
emergent.description: Entities existing primarily in digital/virtual form. Only 4.5% of entities - includes software, digital art, virtual objects, and online phenomena.
emergent.insight: Digital entities often lack Physical Object trait but have Signalling - they transmit, not exist

emergent.name: Minimally Classified
emergent.description: Entities with 1-3 traits - at the edge of classification. These may be underspecified, highly abstract, or represent fundamental primitives.
emergent.insight: 539 entities have ≤3 traits - classification boundary cases or ontological primitives

emergent.name: Ontological Nexus
emergent.description: Entities with 18+ traits - maximally complex objects that touch many ontological categories. Often key cultural or technological artifacts.
emergent.insight: 302 entities have 18+ traits - these are ontological 'hubs' connecting many categories
